```","criticalFindings":[""response": "`Ōśģ Insight ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ`\nA few patterns stand out in this sprint worth noting:\n- The `memoriesInjected` ŌåÆ flywheel hit-rate pipeline is a great example of instrumenting the *write-path* to give the *read-path* precise data instead of inferring from timestamps ŌĆö a common upgrade path in observability systems.\n- The `highlightJSON` function does a correct entity-first escape before regex-based span injection ŌĆö the order matters critically for `{@html}` safety, and the author got it right.\n`ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ`\n\n---\n\n## Code Review ŌĆö Sprint v9.2.0 (commit `feat(v9.0.3)`)\n\n### Overview\n\n25 files changed, +1053/-476. The sprint delivered four capability areas: (1) structured `ReviewFindingMetadata` written into cross-cycle memory, (2) precise flywheel hit-rate via `memoriesInjected` in `audit.json`, (3) search improvements (title/assignee indexing, in-progress cycle fallback), and (4) dashboard polish across branches, memory, agents, and flywheel pages. The commit message claims 20/20 items; the diff is consistent with that scope.\n\n---\n\n### Correctness\n\nThe core logic is sound. `memoriesInjected` is written by `runAuditPhase`, read by `computeMemoryStats`, and the three fallback cases (explicit 0, explicit >0, field absent) are all handled and tested in `flywheel.test.ts`. The search route's in-progress cycle fallback (`sprint-link.json` + `events.jsonl`) is correct and covered by a dedicated test case. The `parseReviewFindingMetadata` function is documented as best-effort, which is appropriate for parsing free-form reviewer output.\n\n---\n\n### Issues\n\n**MAJOR ŌĆö `cancelConfirm` is dead code; \"click outside to dismiss\" never fires**\n`branches/+page.svelte:210` ŌĆö `cancelConfirm` is defined and referenced in a comment (\"Dismiss inline confirm on outside click using window event\"), but there is no `<svelte:window onclick={cancelConfirm}>` or `window.addEventListener` anywhere in the file. The inline per-row confirm can only be dismissed via the explicit cancel button. The intended UX ŌĆö clicking anywhere outside closes it ŌĆö is silently absent. This is a functional regression on a feature that was described as implemented.\n\n**MINOR ŌĆö Sync I/O inside a `filter()` hot path**\n`dashboard-stubs.ts:computeMemoryStats` ŌĆö `readFileSync(auditJsonPath)` is called inside `completedCycles.filter(...)`. For a project with 50+ cycles this executes synchronous disk reads per flywheel poll request. The function is already I/O-heavy, but moving the audit.json reads to a map before the filter would remove the O(N) sync reads from the critical path.\n\n**MINOR ŌĆö Duplicate staleness constant across package boundary**\n`branches/+page.svelte:7` ŌĆö `STALE_THRESHOLD_MS = 3 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000` must stay in sync with the server-side `STALE_DAYS` constant in `dashboard-stubs.ts`. The comment flags it, but a runtime mismatch would cause the UI staleness indicator and server staleness label to disagree silently.\n\n**MINOR ŌĆö `MemoryEntry.metadata` typed as `unknown`, inconsistent with `CycleMemoryEntry`**\n`execute-phase.ts:56` uses `metadata?: unknown` while `memory/types.ts:CycleMemoryEntry` uses the more precise `metadata?: ReviewFindingMetadata | Record<string, unknown>`. These represent the same field on functionally identical shapes. Aligning them would close the gap and let TypeScript flag mis-shaped writes.\n\n---\n\n### Security\n\nNo concerns. The `highlightJSON` function correctly escapes `&`, `<`, `>` before regex-based span injection, so `{@html}` cannot be abused by memory entry values. Span class names are hardcoded strings with no user-controlled interpolation.\n\n---\n\n### Test Coverage\n\nStrong. Three new test files target the exact new behaviors: `audit-phase-memory.test.ts`, `cycles-approval.test.ts`, and `search.test.ts`. The flywheel test additions cover all three `memoriesInjected` cases. The `parseReviewFindingMetadata` function is exported and exercised in `phase-handlers-verification.test.ts`. The in-progress cycle search fallback is covered. No significant gaps observed.\n\n---\n\n### Verdict\n\n```\nVERDICT: REQUEST_CHANGES\nSUMMARY: Solid, well-tested sprint ŌĆö one functional bug (dead cancelConfirm) and\n         two minor quality issues to resolve before merge.\nISSUES:\n  - [MAJOR]  cancelConfirm defined but never bound ŌĆö \"click outside to dismiss\"\n             is silently broken. packages/dashboard/src/routes/branches/+page.svelte:210\n             Fix: add <svelte:window onclick={cancelConfirm} /> after the <svelte:head> block.\n  - [MINOR]  Sync readFileSync per cycle inside computeMemoryStats filter loop.\n             packages/server/src/routes/v5/dashboard-stubs.ts ŌĆö pre-read audit files before filter.\n  - [MINOR]  STALE_THRESHOLD_MS duplicated on client; tie to a shared constant or\n             derive from the API response to prevent silent drift.\n  - [MINOR]  MemoryEntry.metadata: unknown vs CycleMemoryEntry.metadata: ReviewFindingMetadata | ...\n             ŌĆö align the two interface definitions in execute-phase.ts and memory/types.ts.\nSUGGESTIONS:\n  - FILE_PATH_RE in review-phase.ts only matches ~8 root directory prefixes;\n    consider a broader heuristic (any path containing '/') for future-proofing.\n  - The tsconfig.json now depends on .svelte-kit/tsconfig.json being generated.\n    Confirm CI runs `svelte-kit sync` before tsc to avoid phantom build failures.\n```\n\n**Score: 3 / 5** ŌĆö The `cancelConfirm` dead code makes a user-visible feature claim false, which is the kind of thing that fails a demo. Fix the window binding (one line), clean up the minor type inconsistency, and this is a clean 5/5 ship.""],"majorFindings":[""response": "`Ōśģ 